  "prompt": "If I delete someone's conversation (old msgs + new unread message) on WhatsApp without reading it and without opening their chat window, will they receive blue ticks?",
  "response": "No, they will not receive blue ticks if you delete the conversation without opening it, even if it contains unread messages.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Blue ticks indicate that you have read the message.** WhatsApp only sends the read receipt (blue ticks) when you open the chat window and the message is displayed on your screen.\n*   **Deleting the conversation prevents the read receipt from being sent.** Since you didn't open the chat, WhatsApp never registered that you read the message.\n*   **Without accessing the chat window, there is no triggering mechanism for read receipts.** The deleting action has no bearing on whether or not their read receipt will be sent.\n\n**In summary, deleting the conversation will not give the other person any indication (blue ticks) that you ever saw the message.**",
